<html><head><title>Merit System</title></head><body><h2><font color="#99FFOO">Karma</font></h2><br>      The officers want to make sure that everyone is recognized for their contribution to the guild. To accomplish this, we have devised a merit system based on Karma Points. This is a work in progress and will be fine tuned as it is used. For every raid you attend you will receive a minimum number of Karma points (20). Extra Karma is awarded for answering the call to fight in the form of a pick-up raid. Key players in the raid (i.e. main tank, main puller, porters, etc.) will receive extra karma. The Raid Leader will report attendance to the Officers and the Officer in charge of Karma Points will distribute points. You can check these by going to the roster page and clicking on Karma at the top of the page.<br> <br>     Another way you can receive points is to be nominated for them. If you do something extraordinary for someone else in guild, they can nominate you for points by telling an officer who will post it for the Karma Priest. Also, every officer can nominate a guild member for points.  All the officers will be watching for those good deeds. This was changed to officers only to make it easier and quicker for you to get points. You can now /tell an officer in game, instead having to wait till after EQ and posting on website. Nominating other people for points is extremely encouraged.<br><br>     Now the downside, you can also lose Karma Points.  These points can be "cashed in" for things such as raids for you epic, help with quests, armor on raids, spells or equipment from guild bank. The points for each item will be determined on a per item basis. Since trying to list every item or even type of item in the game would be a huge task. You can see the Karma Distribution Officer for information on how to cash these in.<br><br>     As sad as it seems there are other ways to lose points.  Such as KSing, not listening to raid rules, not being a good representative of ED, etc. This is determined by the Karma Priest. If this goes beyond the scope of Karma, then the Guild Leader will be brought in to handle the matter. If someone has negative Karma Points then they will be given a certain amount of time to correct this. If this is not done then that member may be put on suspension, in which all officers will be notified of. If the situation is still not repaired, guild removal is possible. It is your duty to stay informed of guild happenings.  Every guild member should look at the website every few days if not daily. After seven days, of not visiting the site one point of Karma will be deducted everyday. There is of course exceptions to this such as vacations, fire, flood, acts of god and internet service providers. Just email the Karma Priest before your vacation or after you catastrophe and let him/her know what happenned. <br><br><h2><font color="#99FFOO">Medals</font></h2><br> These are pretty self explanatory, but all officers can nominate guild members for medals.  Each of these comes complete with Karma Points and gets added to your roster line up and your signature. These are not yet complete and have not been handed out in there entirety. These are also subject to change.<br><br>1. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_1.gif"> Service Cross - For rare acts of selflessness.<br><br>2. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_2.gif"> Medal of Honor <br><br>3. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_3.gif"> Silver Medallion of Sacrafice - Given out for those who chose to give their lives to further our cause.<br><br>4. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_4.gif"> Order of Valor <br><br>5. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_5.gif"> Recruitment Medal - Medal assigned for every 10 people above 55 recruited to the guild.<br><br>6. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_6.gif"> Order of Meritorious Service - For every year in the guild. <br><br>7. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_7.gif"> Star of Achievement - For outsanding achievement such as epics and titles. <br><br>8. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_10.gif"> Master Warrior's Medal - This is assigned to Melees who have mastered the art of being the MA/Puller. <br> <br>9. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_9.gif"> Bronze Order of Leadership - Guild Officers under lvl 60. <br><br>10. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_11.gif"> Silver Order of Leadership - Guild Officers over lvl 60.<br><br>11. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_12.gif"> Golden Order of Leadership - Guild Leader <br><br>12. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_13.gif"> Service Star - Service above and beyond normal duties of a guild member or officer.<br><br>13. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_16.gif"> Service Star Cluster - for several acts above and beyond the normal duties of a guild member or officer. <br><br>14. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_18.gif"> Crusaders Sword - For every five successful raids lead. <br><br>15. <img src="http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/medals/medal_19.gif"> Defender's Order Cluster <br></body><html>  	</td></tr>	</table>        </td>        <td><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=20 width=20></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><img src=http://www.enchanteddragons.com/files/misc_images/spacer.gif height=20 width=20></td></tr></table></center></html>